{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> βᾰσᾰν-ος</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>touchstone,</b> on which pure gold leaves a yellow streak, ἐς βάσανον δ᾽ ἐλθὼν παρατρίβομαι ὥστε μολύβδῳ χρυσός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 417; χρυσὸν τριβόμενον βασάνῳ [prev. author] 450, compare 1105; παρατρίβεσθαι πρὸς τὰς β. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Coloribus” 793b1, compare “HA” 597b2: _metaphorically_, β. τοῦ ἀρώματος (i.e. τοῦ κινναμώμου) τὴν αἶγα εἶναι 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vita Apollonii” 3.4. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>the use of this as a test,</b> χρυσὸς ἐν β. πρέπει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 10.67 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>test, trial of genuineness,</b> οὐκ ἔστιν μείζων β. χρόνου [[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus] 175.1; δόμεν τι βασάνῳ ἐς ἔλεγχον 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.20; σοφὸς ὤφθη βασάνῳ θ᾽ ἁδύπολις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 510 (Lyric poetry), compare 494; βάσανον λαμβάνειν περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 648b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς β. εἶ χερῶν wilt come to <b>a trial</b> of strength, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 835; πλοῦτος β. ἀνθρώπου τρόπων 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 232.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [νόσου] ἔσχ᾽ ἐπὶ σοὶ βάσανον had <b>experienced</b> it in you, i. e. you had had it first, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 14.1320\">Refs</a>]; βάσανον ὑποκείσονται will be subjected to <b>a test,</b> of candidates, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 58.25 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>inquiry by torture,</b> ἐς πᾶσαν β. ἀπικνέεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.110; εἰς β. αἰτεῖν 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 2.88; ἐξετάσαι διὰ βασάνων “SIG” 780.12 (Astypalaea, Aug.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially at Athens, used to extort evidence from slaves, εἰς β. δέχεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.12; εἰς β. παραδοῦναι 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 8.17; ἐκ βασάνων εἰπεῖν [prev. work] 12 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>confession upon torture,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 53.24, 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 5, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1355b37. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>agony</b> of battle, ἡ κατὰ τὸ ἔργον β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 6.24 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>tortures</b> of disease, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.4.24; compare ἐπάγρυπνος β. 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 211.28; also ψυχικαί [prev. author] 182.19 \">NT+2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>torments</b> of hell,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Luke.16.23. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>trespass-offering,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Ki.6.17.—Oriental word. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G0931","accentedUnicode":"βάσανος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0928G","matchingForm":"βασανίζω","stepTransliteration":"basanizō","gloss":"to torture: torture","_zh_tw_Gloss":"受苦","_es_Gloss":"torturar","_zh_Gloss":"受苦"},{"strongNumber":"G0928H","matchingForm":"βασανίζω","stepTransliteration":"basanizō","gloss":"to torture: anguish","_zh_tw_Gloss":"受苦","_es_Gloss":"torturar","_zh_Gloss":"受苦"},{"strongNumber":"G0929","matchingForm":"βασανισμός","stepTransliteration":"basanismos","gloss":"torment","_zh_tw_Gloss":"痛苦","_es_Gloss":"tormento","_zh_Gloss":"痛苦"},{"strongNumber":"G0930","matchingForm":"βασανιστής","stepTransliteration":"basanistēs","gloss":"torturer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"掌刑","_es_Gloss":"torturador ","_zh_Gloss":"掌刑"},{"strongNumber":"G0939","matchingForm":"βάσις","stepTransliteration":"basis","gloss":"foot","_zh_tw_Gloss":"腳","_es_Gloss":"pie","_zh_Gloss":"脚"}],"shortDef":"torment, severe pain, torture","mediumDef":"torment, severe pain, torture <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>lapis Lydius,</b> a species of stone from Lydia, which being applied to metals was thought to indicate any alloy which might be mixed with them, and therefore used in the trial of metals; hence, <b>examination</b> of a person, especially by torture; in NT <b>torture, torment, severe pain,</b> <ref='Mat.4.24'>Mt. 4:24</ref>; <ref='Luk.16.23, 28'>Lk. 16:23, 28</ref>*","stepGloss":"torment","stepTransliteration":"basanos","count":3,"_es_Definition":"tormento ; dolor","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 折磨, 拷打 (路 16:23,28)<br>2) 劇痛 (太 4:24)","_zh_Definition":"1) 折磨, 拷打 (路 16:23,28)<br>2) 剧痛 (太 4:24)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự đau khổ","_zh_tw_Gloss":"痛苦","_es_Gloss":"tormento","_zh_Gloss":"痛苦"}]}